The paper deals with energy efficiency in wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The focus is on distance computation and graph problems, which suggests categories such as distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of information theory concepts in measuring energy complexity suggests the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the consideration of energy constraints in designing protocols and algorithms suggests the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
